The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Sept. 23: Higher prices of petrol, diesel, fruits and vegetables burned holes in the pockets of consumers and pushed up the rate of inflation to 3.53 per cent in the week ended September 10 from 3.16 per cent in the previous week. The wholesale-based price index inflation increased by 0.4 per cent to 196.4 points owing to costlier primary and fuel products, although prices fell marginally for manufactured items.

 New Delhi, Sept. 23: The Supreme Court today agreed to hear appeals filed by the Madurai income tax commissioner challenging a Madras High Court order that gave relief to a large number of spinning mills. The case had run into controversy due to appearance of finance minister P. Chidambaram?s wife Nalini for the department.

 New Delhi, Sept. 23: Reliance Industries Ltd will invest $5.5-6 billion to raise the capacity of its Jamnagar oil refinery to 60 million tonnes by 2009.

 Mumbai, Sept. 23: The finance ministry is planning to make changes in the provisions of the fringe benefit tax next year so that an untrained mind can also understand it, said sources in the ministry.

 Mumbai, Sept. 23: Infosys Technologies today said it would consider the second quarter results and payment of interim dividend on October 11.




